                                                    <comments>
                    <comment id="12382198" author="oglueck" created="Thu, 10 Mar 2005 18:22:34 +0000"  >Created an attachment (id=14451)&lt;br/&gt;
Proposed fix&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
API Docs of socket.getReceiveBufferSize() and socket.getSendBufferSize() do not&lt;br/&gt;
state if the return value can be negative or not. The fix allocates 2KB of&lt;br/&gt;
buffers if the returned size is &amp;lt;=0.</comment>
                    <comment id="12382199" author="oglueck" created="Thu, 10 Mar 2005 18:30:42 +0000"  >The same code is present in the 3.0 code base. Any fix should be ported.</comment>
                    <comment id="12382200" author="olegk" created="Thu, 10 Mar 2005 18:38:49 +0000"  >Looks good to me.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Oleg</comment>
